<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Document</title>
    <style>
        .about {
            padding: 4rem 2rem;
            background-color: #FFF0F3; /* Soft blush background */
          }
          
          .about-content {
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            align-items: center;
            max-width: 900px;
            margin: 0 auto;
          }
          
          .profile-pic {
            width: 150px;
            height: 150px;
            border-radius: 50%;
            object-fit: cover;
            margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
          }
          
          .about-text {
            text-align: center;
          }
          
          .about-text h2 {
            margin-bottom: 1rem;
            font-size: 2rem;
          }
          
          .about-text p {
            margin-bottom: 1rem;
            line-height: 1.6;
            color: #444;
          }
          
          /* Optional: Make it horizontal on bigger screens */
          @media (min-width: 768px) {
            .about-content {
              flex-direction: row;
              align-items: flex-start;
              gap: 2rem;
            }
            .about-text {
              text-align: left;
            }
          }
          
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <section id="about" class="about">
        <div class="about-content">
          <img src="your-photo.jpg" alt="Your photo" class="profile-pic">
          <div class="about-text">
            <h2>About Me</h2>
            <p>
              Hey there! I'm Chandana T, a creative web developer with a passion for clean design and smooth user experiences. With a background in both graphic design and front-end development, I love building digital spaces that feel alive and human.
            </p>
            <p>
              When I’m not coding, I’m probably sketching, gaming, or wandering around local art museums. I believe in lifelong learning, and I’m always exploring new tools and tech to bring ideas to life.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
      
</body>
</html>
